{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014XnufYuZUjSSgZCt2eBj6V","type":"tool_result","content":"144-├── nodejs.ts         # NodejsProvider implements StackProvider\n145-├── python.ts         # PythonProvider implements StackProvider\n146-├── rust.ts           # RustProvider implements StackProvider\n147:└── __tests__/\n148-```\n149-\n150-**Adding Go:**\n--\n209-├── types.ts          # AgentDriver, AgentProcess, AgentEvent interfaces\n210-├── ralph.ts          # RalphDriver implements AgentDriver (wraps ralph.sh)\n211-├── stream-parser.ts  # Moved from src/lib/ — parses Claude stream-json\n212:└── __tests__/\n213-```\n214-\n215-**What changes:**\n216-- `run.ts` imports `AgentDriver` instead of directly spawning ralph\n217:- `run-helpers.ts` merges into `ralph.ts` (ralph-specific parsing)\n218-- `ralph-prompt.ts` moves into `ralph.ts`\n219-- State files (`.story_retries`, `.flagged_stories`) are managed by TypeScript, not bash\n220-\n--\n270-├── state.ts          # Project config (codeharness.local.md) — stays flat, <200 lines\n271-├── output.ts         # CLI output helpers — stays flat, <50 lines\n272-├── templates.ts      # Template file generation — stays flat, <50 lines\n273:└── __tests__/        # Shared test utilities, fixtures\n274:    ├── fixtures/     # Reusable test data (Cargo.toml variants, state files)\n275:    └── helpers.ts    # Mock factories, state builders\n276-```\n277-\n278-**Import rules:**\n--\n541-\n542-```bash\n543-# In CI pipeline, after build\n544:find src -name '*.ts' -not -path '*__tests__*' -exec awk 'END{if(NR>300)print FILENAME\": \"NR\" lines\"}' {} \\; | tee /dev/stderr | grep -q . && exit 1\n545-```\n546-\n547-**Existing violations get a migration path:** Each over-limit file gets a story in epic-TD to split it. The CI gate starts as a warning, becomes a hard failure after all files are under 300 lines."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VGiy7hMzRe8yYsn5kufEpm","session_id":"fecf2c57-a859-44f9-9426-67