{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RmN2JLBzBu8sKDqWEKeJqR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 12-4: Shared Test Utilities and Fixtures\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want reusable test helpers and fixtures,\n     9→So that tests don't duplicate mock setup across 50+ files.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` exists, when inspected, then it contains: `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `state-builders.ts`, `mock-factories.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` exists, when test files import from it, then common patterns (mock Docker, mock fs, create temp state) are one-liners <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 4 (lib/ Restructuring).** Tests currently duplicate mock setup extensively. Centralizing reduces maintenance and makes tests more readable.\n    19→\n    20→### Fixtures (`src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/`)\n    21→\n    22→**`cargo-toml-variants.ts`**: Pre-built Cargo.toml content strings for testing Rust provider:\n    23→- Minimal binary project\n    24→- Library project with `[lib]`\n    25→- Workspace with multiple members\n    26→- Bevy project with system lib dependencies\n    27→- Project with `[dependencies.opentelemetry]` subsections\n    28→\n    29→**`state-builders.ts`**: Builder pattern for test state objects:\n    30→```typescript\n    31→export function buildSprintState(overrides?: Partial<SprintState>): SprintState\n    32→export function buildStoryState(overrides?: Partial<StoryState>): StoryState\n    33→export function buildEpicState(overrides?: Partial<EpicState>): EpicState\n    34→export function buildSessionState(overrides?: Partial<SessionState>): SessionState\n    35→```\n    36→\n    37→**`mock-factories.ts`**: Factory functions for common mocks:\n    38→```typescript\n    39→export function createMockStackProvider(overrides?: Partial<StackProvider>): StackProvider\n    40→export function createMockAgentDriver(overrides?: Partial<AgentDriver>): AgentDriver\n    41→export function createMockDockerHealth(running: boolean): DockerHealthResult\n    42→```\n    43→\n    44→### Helpers (`src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`)\n    45→\n    46→Common test setup patterns as one-liners:\n    47→```typescript\n    48→export function withMockDocker(running: boolean): void  // mocks execSync('docker info')\n    49→export function withTempState(state: SprintState): { dir: string; cleanup: () => void }\n    50→export function withMockFs(files: Record<string, string>): void  // virtual filesystem\n    51→export function createTempDir(): { path: string; cleanup: () => void }\n    52→```\n    53→\n    54→Audit existing test files to identify the most duplicated patterns. Prioritize the top 5 most-repeated mock setups.\n    55→\n    56→## Files to Change\n    57→\n    58→- `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts` — Create. Cargo.toml test fixtures for various project types\n    59→- `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts` — Create. Builder functions for SprintState, StoryState, EpicState\n    60→- `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.ts` — Create. Factory functions for mock StackProvider, AgentDriver, Docker\n    61→- `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` — Create. One-liner test setup helpers (mock Docker, temp state, mock fs)\n    62→- Existing test files — Refactor to use shared helpers (opportunistic, not required in this story)\n    63→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VGiy7hMzRe8yYsn5kufEpm","session_id":"fecf2c57-a859-44f9-9426-67d9679ac1d8","uuid":"73244aaa-5606-433c-bda9-6b6f4da7890e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:58:26.195Z"}
