here's no proof the utilities actually work. This deviates slightly from the epic's \"not required\" note.\n- **Risk: `vi.mock()` hoisting interaction.** The mock factory pattern requires careful integration. `vi.mock()` calls are hoisted to the top of the file by Vitest. If the factory return value is used directly in `vi.mock('module', () => factoryResult)`, the factory call may execute before imports resolve. The dev agent needs to handle this correctly. I added explicit guidance in the story.\n- **Observation:** The existing story file at this path already had a partial story (status: backlog) with some technical notes and code examples. This was overwritten with the comprehensive version. The original had useful mock factory signatures (`createMockStackProvider`, `createMockAgentDriver`) referencing types from Epic 13 (AgentDriver) which doesn't exist yet. I dropped those in favor of factories matching actual current duplication patterns."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7ffe676d62fa56de (use SendMessage with to: 'a7ffe676d62fa56de' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 50452\ntool_uses: 45\nduration_ms: 280410</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fecf2c57-a859-44f9-9426-67d9679ac1d8","uuid":"e881415f-7dee-4c09-80d6-d88ec168c1ad","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:59:29.214Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-create-story for story 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git a