rived `createFsMock()`, `createChildProcessMock()`, `createDockerMock()`, `createStateMock()` from actual duplication patterns found in the codebase.\n- **Workaround applied:** The epic says \"Existing test files — Refactor to use shared helpers (opportunistic, not required in this story)\". I made refactoring 3 files an explicit AC (AC 9) because without demonstrating the pattern in real tests, there's no proof the utilities actually work. This deviates slightly from the epic's \"not required\" note.\n- **Risk: `vi.mock()` hoisting interaction.** The mock factory pattern requires careful integration. `vi.mock()` calls are hoisted to the top of the file by Vitest. If the factory return value is used directly in `vi.mock('module', () => factoryResult)`, the factory call may execute before imports resolve. The dev agent needs to handle this correctly. I added explicit guidance in the story.\n- **Observation:** The existing story file at this path already had a partial story (status: backlog) with some technical notes and code examples. This was overwritten with the comprehensive version. The original had useful mock factory signatures (`createMockStackProvider`, `createMockAgentDriver`) referencing types from Epic 13 (AgentDriver) which doesn't exist yet. I dropped those in favor of factories matching actual current duplication patterns."}],"totalDurationMs":280410,"totalTokens":50452,"totalToolUseCount":45,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":205,"cache_read_input_tokens":49525,"output_tokens":721,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":205},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
