{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ApBdeVdWe8XvBt2HXWCWHK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"134 test files, 3539 tests, all passing.\n\n---\n\nStory 12-4 implementation is complete and marked for review.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Created 4 shared utility files in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` and `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`\n- Created 4 test files covering all new utilities (46 new tests)\n- Refactored 3 existing test files to use shared utilities (rust.test.ts, feedback.test.ts, selector.test.ts)\n- Updated `src/lib/AGENTS.md` with new shared test utilities section\n- Created exec-plan at `docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md`\n- Updated story file: all tasks checked, status set to \"review\"\n- Full suite: 3539 tests passing, zero regressions, all new files under 300 lines\n\n**Key files:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` (single import point)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Task 5 deviation:** The story specified refactoring `docker.test.ts` but `vi.mock()` hoisting in Vitest prevents using imported factory functions inside `vi.mock()` callbacks (the import isn't initialized when hoisted code runs). `vi.hoisted()` also can't call imported functions. Replaced with `selector.test.ts` which was a better fit for `buildSprintState`/`buildStoryEntry` usage.\n- **Mock factory adoption limitation:** The `createFsMock()`/`createChildProcessMock()` factories are most useful for configuring mock return values (via `vi.mocked()`), not for `vi.mock()` declarations themselves. This is a fundamental Vitest hoisting constraint. The story's dev notes example (`vi.mock('node:fs', () => fsMock)`) only works if `fsMock` is defined with `vi.hoisted()`, which can't call imported functions. Future test files can use the factories but need to define `vi.mock()` calls inline.\n- **No code quality concerns.** All files are clean, typed, and well under 300 lines."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a08c9242c575a0299 (use SendMessage with to: 'a08c9242c575a0299' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 98190\ntool_uses: 71\nduration_ms: 643280</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fecf2c57-a859-44f9-9426-67d9679ac1d8","uuid":"84bd2c38-636e-4643-8743-68001a355f29","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:11:31.240Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a08c9242c575a0299","content":[{"type":"text","text":"134 test files, 3539 tests, all passing.\n\n---\n\nStory 12-4 implementation is complete and marked for review.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Created 4 shared utility files in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` and `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`\n- Created 4 test files covering all new utilities (46 new tests)\n- Refactored 3 existing test files to use shared utilities (rust.test.ts, feedback.test.ts, selector.test.ts)\n- Updated `src/lib/AGENTS.md` with new shared test utilities section\n- Created exec-plan at `docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md`\n- Updated story file: all tasks checked, status set to \"review\"\n- Full suite: 3539 tests passing, zero regressions, all new files under 300 lines\n\n**Key files:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` (single import point)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Task 5 deviation:** The story specified refactoring `docker.test.ts` but `vi.mock()` hoisting in Vitest prevents using imported factory functions inside `vi.mock()` callbacks (the import isn't initialized when hoisted code runs). `vi.hoisted()` also can't call imported functions. Replaced with `selector.test.ts` which was a better fit for `buildSprintState`/`buildStoryEntry` usage.\n- **Mock factory adoption limitation:** The `createFsMock()`/`createChildProcessMock()` factories are most useful for configuring mock return values (via `vi.mocked()`), not for `vi.mock()` declarations themselves. This is a fundamental Vitest hoisting constraint. The story's dev notes example (`vi.mock('node:fs', () => fsMock)`) only works if `fsMock` is defined with `vi.hoisted()`, which can't call imported functions. Future test files can use the factories but need to define `vi.mock()` calls inline.\n- **No code quality concerns.** All files are clean, typed, and well under 300 lines."}],"totalDurationMs":643280,"totalT