{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Sf8nvutEd3wgSFADHdALfh","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fecf2c57-a859-44f9-9426-67d9679ac1d8","uuid":"733dc613-c3f0-4934-ac42-59d3bc934c3f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:12:20.960Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Observation: Existing partial story file was overwritten; original had references to Epic 13 types (AgentDriver) that don't exist yet\n","newString":"- Observation: Existing partial story file was overwritten; original had references to Epic 13 types (AgentDriver) that don't exist yet\n\n### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — dev-story (2026-03-24T18:10:00Z)\n\n- Task 5 deviation: Story specified refactoring docker.test.ts but vi.mock() hoisting prevents using imported factory functions inside vi.mock() callbacks. Replaced with selector.test.ts which was a better fit for buildSprintState/buildStoryEntry usage.\n- Mock factory adoption limitation: createFsMock()/createChildProcessMock() factories are most useful for configuring mock return values (via vi.mocked()), not for vi.mock() declarations. Fundamental Vitest hoisting constraint — story's dev notes example doesn't work as written.\n- No code quality concerns. All files clean, typed, under 300 lines.\n","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — create-story (2026-03-24T11:34:00Z)\n\n- Epic definition had only 1 AC; expanded to 12 ACs by examining codebase\n- Risk: parseStoryKey() returns [Infinity, Infinity] for non-matching keys — edge case needs handling\n- Risk: orphan file deletion (ACs 3-4) is one-way; must delete AFTER successful state write\n- writeStateAtomic() already calls writeSprintStatusYaml() — reconcileState() may cause double YAML generation\n- retry-state.ts has @deprecated comments saying \"will be removed in story 11-3\" for legacy path helpers\n- run.ts still reads ralph/.flagged_stories directly (line 93-101), bypassing sprint-state.json flagged field — must update before file deletion\n\n### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — dev-story (2026-03-24T11:45:00Z)\n\n- Pre-existing ~60 type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced by this story)\n- Readonly mutation workaround: uses JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone + type assertions to mutate SprintState clone\n- YAML always regenerated even in no-op case — cheap but could be optimized to skip if content unchanged\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — create-story (2026-03-24T12:01:00Z)\n\n- Workflow file was `workflow.yaml` not `workflow.md` — skill invocation message referenced `.md` but only `.yaml` existed\n- Subagent was instructed not to modify sprint-status.yaml; main agent had to update manually\n- Risk: runner.ts may push past 300 lines if all private helpers are large (~230 line estimate is rough)\n- Risk: AC11 (integration-required) tests e2e CLI behavior identity, requires real project with test runner configured\n- `coverage.ts` is 633 lines (not 617 as stated in architecture-v3.md — grew since doc was written)\n- This establishes the first domain subdirectory pattern in src/lib/ — stories 12-2 through 12-4 will follow it\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — dev-story (2026-03-24T12:04:00Z)\n\nNo issues reported (subagent reported \"None\").\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — code-review (2026-03-24T12:14:00Z)\n\n- HIGH: runner.ts statement coverage at 78.15% (below 80% per-file floor). Fixed — now 95.79% (+11 new tests)\n- MEDIUM (unfixed tech debt): `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts but not from index.ts barrel. Used only by evaluator.ts as sibling import.\n- LOW: `error: required option '--story <key>' not specified` noise during `codeharness coverage` runs from other commands registering at startup\n- No integration test exercises full `runCoverage` pipeline end-to-end (AC11 integration-required)\n- index.ts and types.ts show 0% coverage (pure type exports, expected)\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — verification (2026-03-24T16:33:00Z)\n\n- Docker Desktop daemon not running — blocked black-box verification\n- Attempted Docker start (`open -a Docker`) — did not come up within 100 seconds\n- Workaround: Used unit-testable verification (direct CLI checks) for all cli-verifiable ACs\n- AC11 (integration-required) escalated — genuinely needs Docker for CLI behavior identity testing\n- Proof format issue: initial proof used plain ``` blocks, parser requires ```bash + ```output pairs\n- `codeharness verify` precondition check requires `tests_passed` session flag — had to run `codeharness coverage` first to set it\n- `codeharness coverage --check-only` misparses test counts as \"0 passed, 0 failed\" (output format mismatch)\n\n### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — create-story (2026-03-24T12:43:00Z)\n\n- Epic definition lists otlp.ts as 422 lines but actual measurement shows 453 lines — used actual\n- Epic retrospective (epic-12-retrospective.md) describes a different Epic 12 (verification pipeline integrity) — numbering reused after renumbering\n- Epic ACs extremely terse (only 2 ACs for 4 file splits) — expanded to 13 ACs to match 12-1 granularity\n- Risk: `backends.ts` in observability/ may require new code (ObservabilityBackend interface) not extractable from otlp.ts\n- Risk: `cleanup.ts` in docker/ references functions that may live in `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` instead of docker.ts\n- Risk: `doc-health.ts` at 832 lines — `scanDocHealth` alone is ~196 lines, scanner.ts may exceed 300 lines\n- Test files collectively 3,204 lines — larger than source files (2,253 lines). Test reorg is significant work\n\n### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — dev-story (2026-03-24T13:06:00Z)\n\n- Circular dependency in doc-health: scanner.ts and staleness.ts have mutual dependency. Resolved by extracting shared utilities to types.ts\n- Dynamic import in teardown.ts (`await import('../lib/docker.js')`) missed by initial sed-based import replacement — fixed manually\n- Test files kept as single files moved to __tests__/ dirs rather than split per-module as AC10 suggested (no functional need)\n- beads.ts 300-line limit forced moving types/functions to story-files.ts — story specified them in beads.ts\n- doc-health/types.ts extra file not in story — necessary for circular dependency resolution\n- backends.ts is entirely new code (no backend abstraction in original otlp.ts)\n- cleanup.ts is stubs only — cleanup logic lives in src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts\n\n### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — code-review (2026-03-24T17:19:00Z)\n\n- HIGH: docker/cleanup.ts had 0% coverage — FIXED (added cleanup.test.ts)\n- HIGH: observability/backends.ts had 0% coverage — FIXED (added backends.test.ts)\n- LOW (unfixed): doc-health/index.ts leaks internal utility functions through barrel\n- LOW (unfixed): doc-health/types.ts duplicates SOURCE_EXTENSIONS constant (3 copies)\n- LOW (unfixed): docker/cleanup.ts and observability/backends.ts are placeholder stubs\n- Coverage gap: test files not reorganized per AC10 (monolithic test files moved as-is)\n- staleness.ts at 284 lines, close to 300-line limit\n\n### 12-3-move-status-logic-to-module — dev-story (2026-03-24T13:38:00Z)\n\nNo issues reported (subagent reported \"None\").\n\n### 12-3-move-status-logic-to-module — code-review (2026-03-24T13:49:00Z)\n\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Unused import `isSharedStackRunning` in formatters.ts — dead code from extraction\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Unused type import `DockerHealthResult` in formatters.ts\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing mock for `modules/verify/index.js` in status.test.ts — tests relied on graceful error handling\n- LOW (unfixed): No dedicated unit tests for formatters.ts or drill-down.ts at module level\n- LOW (unfixed): `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` independently call report generation — potential duplication\n- Coverage gap: `getValidationProgress` integration path only implicitly tested\n\n### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — create-story (2026-03-24T17:55:00Z)\n\n- Ambiguity in epic definition: 2 terse ACs expanded to 10 based on architecture-v3.md and codebase analysis\n- Workaround: Made refactoring 3 files an explicit AC (AC 9) despite epic saying \"not required\" — needed to prove utilities work\n- Risk: `vi.mock()` hoisting interaction with mock factories needs careful handling by dev agent\n- Observation: Existing partial story file was overwritten; original had references to Epic 13 types (AgentDriver) that don't exist yet\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":95,"oldLines":3,"newStart":95,"newLines":9,"lines":[" - Workaround: Made refactoring 3 files an explicit AC (AC 9) despite epic saying \"not required\" — needed to prove utilities work"," - Risk: `vi.mock()` hoisting interaction with mock factories needs careful handling by dev agent"," - Observation: Existing partial story file was overwritten; original had references to Epic 13 types (AgentDriver) that don't exist yet","+","+### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — dev-story (2026-03-24T18:10:00Z)","+","+- Task 5 deviation: Story specified refactoring docker.test.ts but vi.mock() hoisting prevents using imported factory functions inside vi.mock() callbacks. Replaced with selector.test.ts which was a better fit for buildSprintState/buildStoryEntry usage.","+- Mock factory adoption limitation: createFsMock()/createChildProcessMock() factories are most useful for configuring mock return values (via vi.mocked()), not for vi.mock() declarations. Fundamental Vitest hoisting constraint — story's dev notes example doesn't work as written.","+- No code quality concerns. All files clean, typed, under 300 lines."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
