{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TzNuaKm4zDZuGviDJFhrXN","type":"tool_result","content":"  1577→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-24 (Session 10, Evening)\n  1578→\n  1579→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n  1580→**Session:** 10 (continuation, evening)\n  1581→**Timestamp:** 2026-03-24T17:31:00Z\n  1582→\n  1583→---\n  1584→\n  1585→## 1. Session Summary\n  1586→\n  1587→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages |\n  1588→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|\n  1589→| 12-3-move-status-logic-to-module | Epic 12 (File Size Reduction) | done | dev-story, code-review (3 fixes), verification (passed) |\n  1590→\n  1591→**Scope:** Single story — extracted the monolithic `status.ts` command (745 lines) into `src/modules/status/` with 4 module files. Command file reduced to 56 lines (thin shell delegating to module).\n  1592→\n  1593→**Test results:** 3,493 tests passing, 97.09% coverage. No regressions.\n  1594→\n  1595→**Net progress:** Epic 12 now 3/4 stories done (12-4 remains in backlog).\n  1596→\n  1597→---\n  1598→\n  1599→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1600→\n  1601→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n  1602→\n  1603→| Severity | Issue | Fixed? |\n  1604→|----------|-------|--------|\n  1605→| MEDIUM | Unused import `isSharedStackRunning` in formatters.ts — dead code leftover from extraction | Yes |\n  1606→| MEDIUM | Unused type import `DockerHealthResult` in formatters.ts | Yes |\n  1607→| MEDIUM | Missing mock for `modules/verify/index.js` in status.test.ts — tests passed only because error handling was graceful | Yes |\n  1608→\n  1609→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n  1610→\n  1611→| Issue | Status |\n  1612→|-------|--------|\n  1613→| No dedicated unit tests for formatters.ts or drill-down.ts at module level | Unfixed — covered only via integration through status command tests |\n  1614→| `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` independently call report generation — potential duplication | Unfixed — LOW severity, no functional impact |\n  1615→| `getValidationProgress` integration path only implicitly tested | Unfixed — coverage gap, no dedicated assertion |\n  1616→\n  1617→### Code Quality Concerns\n  1618→\n  1619→- All 3 MEDIUM issues from code review were fixed before verification.\n  1620→- 2 LOW issues remain unfixed (no dedicated module-level tests, report generation duplication). Both are acceptable tech debt for a refactoring story.\n  1621→\n  1622→### Verification Observations\n  1623→\n  1624→- Verification used **unit-testable** tier for both ACs (both were cli-verifiable).\n  1625→- Had to add explicit `**Tier:** unit-testable` marker to proof document for `blackBoxPass` to parse correctly — the verification parser requires this metadata.\n  1626→- No Docker needed for this story (unlike 12-1 which was blocked by Docker Desktop being down).\n  1627→\n  1628→### Tooling / Infrastructure Issues\n  1629→\n  1630→- **Stale AGENTS.md files:** 4 directories from prior story 12-2 had stale AGENTS.md files that needed updating. These were leftover from the split operations — the dev subagent for 12-2 did not regenerate them.\n  1631→\n  1632→---\n  1633→\n  1634→## 3. What Went Well\n  1635→\n  1636→- **Clean extraction:** 745-line monolith reduced to 56-line command + 4 focused modules with no behavioral changes.\n  1637→- **Zero test regressions:** All 3,493 tests pass. Coverage held at 97.09%.\n  1638→- **Code review caught real issues:** All 3 MEDIUM findings (unused imports, missing mock) were genuine problems that could mask future bugs.\n  1639→- **Fast cycle:** dev-story reported zero issues. Code review found and fixed problems efficiently. Verification passed cleanly.\n  1640→- **Verification tier selection was correct:** unit-testable tier was appropriate — no need to spin up Docker for a pure refactoring story.\n  1641→\n  1642→---\n  1643→\n  1644→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1645→\n  1646→- **Stale AGENTS.md from prior story:** 4 directories needed AGENTS.md fixes that should have been caught during 12-2's code review or verification. This was cleanup debt from the previous session leaking into this one.\n  1647→- **Proof format requirement:** The `blackBoxPass` parser required a `**Tier:** unit-testable` annotation that wasn't obvious. This has now tripped up multiple stories (also seen in 12-1 with `bash`/`output` block requirements).\n  1648→\n  1649→---\n  1650→\n  1651→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1652→\n  1653→### Patterns to Repeat\n  1654→\n  1655→- **Single-story sessions for refactoring:** Focused scope with one extraction story works well. Clean in, clean out.\n  1656→- **Fix all code review findings before verification:** The 3 MEDIUM fixes prevented false confidence in the test suite.\n  1657→- **Dev subagent reporting \"no issues\" is a positive signal** — when the extraction is straightforward, the dev phase should be fast and clean.\n  1658→\n  1659→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1660→\n  1661→- **Not regenerating AGENTS.md after file splits:** Every story that moves files between directories must update AGENTS.md in affected directories. This should be an explicit AC or a post-dev checklist item.\n  1662→- **Assuming proof format is self-evident:** The verification parser has specific format requirements (`**Tier:**`, `bash`/`output` fenced blocks). These need to be documented or enforced by the create-story template.\n  1663→\n  1664→---\n  1665→\n  1666→## 6. Action Items\n  1667→\n  1668→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  1669→\n  1670→_None — all MEDIUM issues were already fixed during this session._\n  1671→\n  1672→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  1673→\n  1674→| Item | Source |\n  1675→|------|--------|\n  1676→| Add AGENTS.md regeneration as explicit step in file-split stories | 12-2 and 12-3 both needed manual AGENTS.md fixes |\n  1677→| Document verification proof format requirements (Tier marker, bash/output blocks) | Hit in 12-1 and 12-3 |\n  1678→| Add module-level unit tests for formatters.ts and drill-down.ts | Code review LOW finding |\n  1679→\n  1680→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n  1681→\n  1682→| Item | Source |\n  1683→|------|--------|\n  1684→| Deduplicate report generation between `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` | Code review LOW finding |\n  1685→| Add explicit test for `getValidationProgress` integration path | Coverage gap noted in review |\n  1686→| story 12-4 (shared test utilities/fixtures) remains — last story in Epic 12 | Sprint status |\n  1687→\n  1688→---\n  1689→\n  1690→### Sprint Velocity (updated)\n  1691→\n  1692→| Metric | Value |\n  1693→|--------|-------|\n  1694→| Stories completed this session | 1 (12-3) |\n  1695→| Stories completed today (cumulative) | 6 (11-1, 11-2, 11-3, 12-1, 12-2, 12-3) |\n  1696→| Epic 12 progress | 3/4 stories done |\n  1697→| Epics closed today | 1 (Epic 11) |\n  1698→| Total tests | 3,493 passing |\n  1699→| Coverage | 97.09% |\n  1700→| Lines extracted this session | 745 -> 56 command + 4 modules |\n  1701→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01E1Q26yaZEFbxdMYvY9VEFm","session_id":"fecf2c57-a859-44f9-9426-67d9679ac1d8","uuid":"4e920252-6f69-4151-a557-152a7374b3b7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:13:26.290Z"}
